casebody.data:
First Department,

July, 1973

(July 3, 1973) Jerry Dross, Appellant, v. Bess Myerson, as Commissioner of the Department of Consumer Affairs of the City of New York, Respondent.

Judgment, Supreme Court, New York County, entered on May 9, 1973, unanimously vacated, and under the provisions of CPLR 7804 (subd. [g]) this court treats the proceeding as if it had been transferred to it in the first instance, and the determination of respondent Commissioner dated May 17, 1972, is confirmed, without costs and without disbursements. No opinion. Concur — Markewich, J. P., Murphy, Lane and Tilzer, JJ.
